16/01/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Authorities have volunteered to house prisoners from Guantanamo Bay, media reported on Thursday (January 15th).
Sweden, Portugal and Switzerland have also agreed to receive Guantanamo detainees when the facility closes.
In other news Thursday, Albania and Montenegro launched a joint patrol mission on their common border.
The countries seek to boost their fight against cross-border crime.
(Start, Top Channel, News 24 - 15/01/09)
